This is code that was posted on StuyPulse on GItHub that I modified to run against our robot. I am able to run it on the robot and needed to verify three things:

  1. I presume both back wheels (back left and back right) should be spinning and turning fast. I presume both front wheels (front left and front right) should be spinning and turning more slowly than the back for the SYSID test purposes. Correct?
  2. We are not finding any logs on the Robo Rio 2.0 after running the test in DriveStation after deploying the code and Enabling the Robot. Robot Code is green so the Robo Rio should be running the SYSID routine. Any idea why we are not seeing any logs? Am I missing adding logging in my code?
  3. I presume we have the right code to get the data needed for “Robot MOI” for PathPlanner. IE ka_linear and ka_angular. Correct?
